        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 26 at 3:53PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 353 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 6 miles
north of Mcalester, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Arrowhead State Park...           Raiford...
Canadian...                       Indianola...
Crowder...                        Mcalester...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
